3300 Building Founded: 1968Owner: Andy Varat, 64Employees: Incubator housing eight independent businesses with 100-plus employees overallAnnual revenues: Estimated $30+ million combined for fiscal year 2016Location: 3300 NW 41st St.About: Andy Varat has converted his family‚Äôs longtime warehouse facilities into an incubator with eight independent fashion businesses operating under one roof.Contact: Andy.Varat@gmail.com 
Education in fashion Among the offerings in Miami-Dade:Miami Dade CollegeMDC has launched a new degree program that will help stimulate the growth of the fashion industry in Miami. Housed under the newly formed Miami Fashion Institute, its two-year associate‚Äôs degree program in fashion design and merchandising is being launched this semester. www.mdc.edu/fashiondesign. At MDC‚Äôs Wolfson Campus in downtown Miami.Miami International University of Art & DesignLocally, Miami International University of Art & Design, part of the Arts Institutes, offers associate‚Äôs and bachelor‚Äôs degree programs in fashion design and fashion marketing, but at a higher cost. www.artinstitutes.edu/miami (click on fashion). At 1501 Biscayne Blvd., Suite 100, Miami.
